<body>
Reports a return value of a function that doesn't return anything.
Calling of such functions always produces an <code>undefined</code> value and such assignment may indicate an error. <p>Example:</p>
<pre><code>
let a = console.log('foo');
</code></pre>
<br/>
The following usages are ignored:
<ul>
  <li>Inside a return statement</li>
  <li>In some binary operations</li>
  <li>For overridden non-void functions</li>
</ul>
</body>
</html>